    "engine": "knitr",
    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Bacteroidetes/Firmicutes ratio\"\nauthor:\n  - name: Muluh\n---\n\n\n\n\n## Bacteroidetes/Firmicutes ratio\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\n### Group-wise comparisons\n\n-   **Taxonomic level:** Phylum\n-   **Group variable:** diet\n-   **Multiple testing correction:** fdr\n-   **Statistical test** Wilcoxon\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell layout-align=\"center\"}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n#### Table of the top findings\n\n#### Across-group\n\n##### Before treatment\n\n-   Multiple testing correction: **fdr**\n-   Statistical test: **Wilcoxon**\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"datatables html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-4e01a338be3fc7fc020f\" style=\"width:100%;height:auto;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-4e01a338be3fc7fc020f\">{\"x\":{\"filter\":\"none\",\"vertical\":false,\"caption\":\"<caption>Table of  Bacteroidetes/Firmicutes before Treatment<\\/caption>\",\"data\":[[\"oat\"],[\"rice\"],[0.32],[0.29],[-0.12],[0.41]],\"container\":\"<table class=\\\"display\\\">\\n  <thead>\\n    <tr>\\n      <th>group1<\\/th>\\n      <th>group2<\\/th>\\n      <th>mean1<\\/th>\\n      <th>mean2<\\/th>\\n      <th>log2FC<\\/th>\\n      <th>p.adj<\\/th>\\n    <\\/tr>\\n  <\\/thead>\\n<\\/table>\",\"options\":{\"pageLength\":6,\"dom\":\"Bfrtip\",\"columnDefs\":[{\"targets\":5,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatSignif(data, 3, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":2,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":3,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":4,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"className\":\"dt-right\",\"targets\":[2,3,4,5]},{\"name\":\"group1\",\"targets\":0},{\"name\":\"group2\",\"targets\":1},{\"name\":\"mean1\",\"targets\":2},{\"name\":\"mean2\",\"targets\":3},{\"name\":\"log2FC\",\"targets\":4},{\"name\":\"p.adj\",\"targets\":5}],\"order\":[],\"autoWidth\":false,\"orderClasses\":false,\"lengthMenu\":[6,10,25,50,100]}},\"evals\":[\"options.columnDefs.0.render\",\"options.columnDefs.1.render\",\"options.columnDefs.2.render\",\"options.columnDefs.3.render\"],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe B/F ratio was slightly lower in the rice group `(mean = 0.29)` compared to the oat group `(mean = 0.32)`. The fold change `(log2FC = -0.12)` suggests a small decrease in the ratio for the rice group. However, this difference was not statistically significant `(p.adj = 0.410)`, indicating no strong evidence of a baseline difference between the two diet groups.\n\n##### After treatment\n\n-   Multiple testing correction: **fdr**\n-   Statistical test: **Wilcoxon**\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"datatables html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-cd3c13a11a0bdafa6b13\" style=\"width:100%;height:auto;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-cd3c13a11a0bdafa6b13\">{\"x\":{\"filter\":\"none\",\"vertical\":false,\"caption\":\"<caption>Table of Bacteroidetes/Firmicutes after Treatment<\\/caption>\",\"data\":[[\"oat\"],[\"rice\"],[0.33],[0.33],[-0.02],[0.68]],\"container\":\"<table class=\\\"display\\\">\\n  <thead>\\n    <tr>\\n      <th>group1<\\/th>\\n      <th>group2<\\/th>\\n      <th>mean1<\\/th>\\n      <th>mean2<\\/th>\\n      <th>log2FC<\\/th>\\n      <th>p.adj<\\/th>\\n    <\\/tr>\\n  <\\/thead>\\n<\\/table>\",\"options\":{\"pageLength\":6,\"dom\":\"Bfrtip\",\"columnDefs\":[{\"targets\":5,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatSignif(data, 3, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":2,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":3,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":4,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"className\":\"dt-right\",\"targets\":[2,3,4,5]},{\"name\":\"group1\",\"targets\":0},{\"name\":\"group2\",\"targets\":1},{\"name\":\"mean1\",\"targets\":2},{\"name\":\"mean2\",\"targets\":3},{\"name\":\"log2FC\",\"targets\":4},{\"name\":\"p.adj\",\"targets\":5}],\"order\":[],\"autoWidth\":false,\"orderClasses\":false,\"lengthMenu\":[6,10,25,50,100]}},\"evals\":[\"options.columnDefs.0.render\",\"options.columnDefs.1.render\",\"options.columnDefs.2.render\",\"options.columnDefs.3.render\"],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe B/F ratio was identical between the oat and rice groups (`mean = 0.33` for both) after treatment. The fold change `(log2FC = -0.02)` indicates minimal difference. The p-value `(p.adj = 0.680)` confirms that there is no statistically significant difference in the B/F ratio between the two diet groups post-treatment.\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell layout-align=\"center\"}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ratio_files/figure-html/viz-div_change-1.png){fig-align='center' width=480}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n#### Within-group\n\n##### Paired treatment\n\n-   Multiple testing correction: **fdr**\n-   Statistical test: **`paired r test`**\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"datatables html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-e6294015dcf0e0037c3b\" style=\"width:100%;height:auto;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-e6294015dcf0e0037c3b\">{\"x\":{\"filter\":\"none\",\"vertical\":false,\"caption\":\"<caption>Table of Bacteroidetes/Firmicutes paired between timepoint (1 and 2)<\\/caption>\",\"data\":[[\"oat\",\"rice\"],[0.32,0.29],[0.33,0.33],[0.28,1.07],[0.8,0.37]],\"container\":\"<table class=\\\"display\\\">\\n  <thead>\\n    <tr>\\n      <th>diet<\\/th>\\n      <th>mean1<\\/th>\\n      <th>mean2<\\/th>\\n      <th>log2FC<\\/th>\\n      <th>p.value<\\/th>\\n    <\\/tr>\\n  <\\/thead>\\n<\\/table>\",\"options\":{\"pageLength\":4,\"dom\":\"Bfrtip\",\"columnDefs\":[{\"targets\":4,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatSignif(data, 3, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":1,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":2,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"targets\":3,\"render\":\"function(data, type, row, meta) {\\n    return type !== 'display' ? data : DTWidget.formatRound(data, 2, 3, \\\",\\\", \\\".\\\", null);\\n  }\"},{\"className\":\"dt-right\",\"targets\":[1,2,3,4]},{\"name\":\"diet\",\"targets\":0},{\"name\":\"mean1\",\"targets\":1},{\"name\":\"mean2\",\"targets\":2},{\"name\":\"log2FC\",\"targets\":3},{\"name\":\"p.value\",\"targets\":4}],\"order\":[],\"autoWidth\":false,\"orderClasses\":false,\"lengthMenu\":[4,10,25,50,100]}},\"evals\":[\"options.columnDefs.0.render\",\"options.columnDefs.1.render\",\"options.columnDefs.2.render\",\"options.columnDefs.3.render\"],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\nIn the oat diet group, the B/F ratio slightly increased from `0.32 to 0.33` (log2FC = `0.28`, p = `0.800`), indicating no significant change over time.\n\nIn the rice diet group, the B/F ratio increased from `0.29 to 0.33` (log2FC = `1.07`, p = `0.370`), but this change was not statistically significant.\n\nHence, B/F ratio remained relatively stable over time for both diet groups, with no significant shifts from before to after treatment.\n\n### LMM\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n\n\n-   Multiple testing correction: **FDR**\n-   Statistical test: **paired Wilcoxon**\n-   Formula used: **~ diet * timepoint + (1 | id)**\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ratio_files/figure-html/table-fixed-fx-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:none;\">\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-top: double; text-align:center; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; padding:0.2cm;  text-align:left; \">&nbsp;</th>\n<th colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-top: double; text-align:center; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold; padding:0.2cm; \">y</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\" text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal;  text-align:left; \">Predictors</td>\n<td style=\" text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal;  \">Estimates</td>\n<td style=\" text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal;  \">CI</td>\n<td style=\" text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal;  \">p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; \">(Intercept)</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">&#45;1.93</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">&#45;2.59&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;-1.27</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \"><strong>&lt;0.001</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; \">diet [rice]</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">&#45;0.51</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">&#45;1.44&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;0.43</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">0.285</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; \">time</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">&#45;0.02</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">&#45;0.41&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;0.37</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">0.907</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; \">diet [rice] × time</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">0.22</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">&#45;0.33&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;0.77</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:center;  \">0.427</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"4\" style=\"font-weight:bold; text-align:left; padding-top:.8em;\">Random Effects</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm;\">&sigma;<sup>2</sup></td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm; text-align:left;\" colspan=\"3\">0.67</td>\n</tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm;\">&tau;<sub>00</sub> <sub>id</sub></td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm; text-align:left;\" colspan=\"3\">0.58</td>\n\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm;\">ICC</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm; text-align:left;\" colspan=\"3\">0.47</td>\n\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm;\">N <sub>id</sub></td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm; text-align:left;\" colspan=\"3\">71</td>\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm; border-top:1px solid;\">Observations</td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm; text-align:left; border-top:1px solid;\" colspan=\"3\">140</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; text-align:left; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm;\">Marginal R<sup>2</sup> / Conditional R<sup>2</sup></td>\n<td style=\" padding:0.2cm; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-top:0.1cm; padding-bottom:0.1cm; text-align:left;\" colspan=\"3\">0.010 / 0.473</td>\n</tr>\n\n</table>\n\n`````\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Intercept is highly significant (Estimate = `-1.93`, `p = 8.67e-8`), suggesting a clear baseline effect before treatment.\n\n\nThe dietrice term, representing the difference between the rice and oat groups, is not significant (Estimate = `-0.51`, p = `0.286`).\n\nThe time term, indicating any overall time effect, is also not significant (Estimate = `-0.02`, `p = 0.907`).\n\nThe interaction between diet and time (dietrice:time) shows a non-significant effect (Estimate = `0.22`, `p = 0.428`), indicating that the effect of diet over time is not statistically different for rice vs. oat.\n\n## Data Summary\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nclass: TreeSummarizedExperiment \ndim: 18 140 \nmetadata(1): agglomerated_by_rank\nassays(1): relabundance\nrownames(18): Actinobacteria Ascomycota ... Thaumarchaeota\n  Verrucomicrobia\nrowData names(9): kingdom phylum ... strain clade_name\ncolnames(140): AE1332 AE2332 ... VK1336 VK2336\ncolData names(17): sample id ... bact_firm_ratio bfratio\nreducedDimNames(0):\nmainExpName: NULL\naltExpNames(0):\nrowLinks: NULL\nrowTree: NULL\ncolLinks: NULL\ncolTree: NULL\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n",
